name: BAJU PENGHULU - TRADITIONAL CLOTHING OF WEST SUMATRA (INDONESIA)
description:
Baju Penghulu are traditional West Sumatran clothes that are identical in dark colors sprinkled with gold and complete with head coverings. This deta or headgear is in the form of a cloth loop that produces a lot of wrinkles. The more wrinkles, the more attractive it looks.
